            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": ">The mebibyte is closely related to the megabyte (MB). This can either be a synonym for mebibyte, or refer to 10<sup>6</sup> bytes = 1,000,000 bytes, depending on context [1]\r\n\r\n[[1]](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mebibyte). Unfortunately the references are dead links.  But most people I've ever interacted with always think in 1024 of something, but don't use the \"mebi|gibi|etc\" versions."
