            "body": "@carc1n0gen , the quote you provided ends with:\r\n> ... The two numbers are relatively close together, but mistaking the two has nevertheless led to problems.\r\n\r\nThis \"mistake\" led me to problems, which wouldn't be arise if 1000<sup>2</sup> was used rather than 1024<sup>2</sup>.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, because docs are meant for educational and guidance, it is better to stick with the [standards](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IEEE_1541-2002), rather than unambiguous prefixes - [unless pointed out](https://physics.nist.gov/cuu/Units/binary.html).\r\n\r\nEither way, the docs should clarify it better."
